Ahun community in Efon Kingdom, Ekiti State, has celebrated the yearly ‘Ewi Olojo,’ otherwise known as Oloere Festival, has been celebrated in accordance with COVID-19 protocols. The celebration was presided over by the community head, Alahun Jacob Adelowo. Usually, aside from the Ahun people who owns and celebrates the annual festival, visitors always come from within and outside Efon-Alaaye for the celebration. The highlights of the occasion included prayers for the community and the entire kingdom. The Alahun, who wished the good people of AHUN Community home and abroad a happy Oloere Festival celebration, urged them to stay safe.